Updated for Hybrid 7 (2000/12/28)

When you type /version you will often see something like this:
*** hybrid-7(alpha)(20010117_13). irc.vchan GHCiIMp TS3ow

Ever wondered what those funny chars mean after the version number? Well
here they are:

'C'	CMDLINE_CONFIG
'D'	DEBUGMODE
'G'	GLINES
'H'	HUB
'i'     SHOW_INVISIBLE_LUSERS (to opers)
'I'     NO_DEFAULT_INVISIBLE
'M'     IDLE_FROM_MSG
'p'	CRYPT_OPER_PASSWORD
'P'	CRYPT_LINK_PASSWORD
'Y'	USE_SYSLOG

'TS'    Supports TS
'3'     TS Version 3
'o'     TS Only
'w'     TS Warnings
